M. charantia have been reported to exhibit anti-diabetic, anthelmintic, abortifacient, anti-bacterial, anti-viral, hypoglycemic agents and chemo-preventive functions (
Grover and Yadav, 2004; 
Costa et al., 2010; 
Ghosh, 2014; 
Bulbul, 2016; 
Dzotam et al., 2016; 
Ludidi et al., 2019; Kulkarni ei al. 2021). The fruits and leaves of 
M. charantia display various biological activities including anti-diabetic, anti-rheumatic, and anti-ulcer, anti-inflammatory and anti-tumor (
Dzotam et al., 2016). 
M. charantia contains various chemicals that have a hypoglycemic activity which reduces the amount of sugar in the blood, furthermore it stimulates appetite and helps in the entire digestion process. 
M. charantia is used for the treatment of digestive problems (
Ludidi et al., 2019).
